function [CPD] = cpi2cpd(CPI,size,distance)% function [CPD] = cpi2cpd(CPI,size,distance)%% Converts cycles per image [CPI] into cycles per degree of visual% angle [CPD], using [CPI], the [size] of the display, and the% viewing [distance]. %% Assumes [size] and [distance] are in the same units.%% March 23, 1997.  JMG  PJB  ABS   U of Toronto Vision LabCPD = CPI/rad2deg(atan(size/distance));return